B. Japan, local transmission
Date: Sat 15 Feb 2020
Source: NHK World [edited]
https://www3.nhk.or.jp/nhkworld/en/news/20200216_05/


Health experts confirmed new cases of the coronavirus across Japan on Saturday [15 Feb 2020]. The total number of infections is now over 330, including 285 on a quarantined cruise ship.

Tokyo Metropolitan Government officials said on Saturday [15 Feb 2020] that 8 more people had been confirmed to be infected with the virus there; 7 of them were found when the authorities were investigating a taxi driver who was earlier confirmed to be infected.

And in the central prefecture of Aichi, a woman has been confirmed to have the virus. Her husband was confirmed on the previous day [14 Feb 2020].

In the western prefecture of Wakayama, 3 more people tested positive on Saturday [15 Feb 2020]. They are a doctor, his wife, and an inpatient at a hospital. Those cases bring the number of patients to 5 related to the hospital. Officials in Wakayama are now testing all of the doctors and staff at the hospital, as well as anyone who has had contact with the infected patients.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail Rapporteur Kunihiko Iizuka

[In the above description of cases, all but one have been connected to contact with persons previously confirmed as infected; the one outlier is one of the 8 cases recently confirmed in Tokyo where no mention is made of known contact with other confirmed cases of COVID-19.

It appears as though there has been transmission ongoing in Wakayama associated with the positive COVID-19 case in a physician. So far there have been 2 patients in the hospital where the index case worked, another doctor and his wife. Obvious concern surrounds the transmission in the hospital as other coronaviruses (SARS-CoV and MERS-CoV) were (and still are in the case of MERS-CoV) associated with nosocomial outbreaks.

A good map showing the prefectures of Japan can be found at https://www.digi-joho.com/japan-maps.html. It does not include the Okinawa Islands, though.

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map of Japan: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=6993525,156 - Mod.MPP]

